A timeline of the life of [[Frodo Baggins]] in the [[Third Age]].

==[[Third Age 2968|2968]]==
*[[22 September]]: Birth of Frodo Baggins.

==[[Third Age 2980|2980]]==
*Death of Frodo's parents, [[Drogo Baggins]] and [[Primula Brandybuck]].

==[[Third Age 2989|2989]]==
*Frodo is adopted by [[Bilbo Baggins]] and moves to [[Bag End]] around this time.

==[[Third Age 3001|3001]]==
*22 September: Frodo comes of age and inherits Bag End and the [[The One Ring|Ring]] from Bilbo.

==[[Third Age 3004|3004]]==
*[[Gandalf]] visits Frodo in the [[The Shire|Shire]] several times over the next four years.

==[[Third Age 3008|3008]]==
*Gandalf visits Frodo for the last time for many years.

==[[Third Age 3018|3018]]==
*[[12 April]]: Gandalf arrives at Bag End.
*[[13 April]]: Frodo learns he has the One Ring and decides to leave the Shire.

*[[22 September]]: Frodo turns 50.
*[[23 September]]: Frodo leaves Bag End.
*[[24 September]]: Frodo is nearly caught twice by one of the [[Nazgûl]] and meets [[Gildor]] in the [[Woody End]].
*[[25 September]]: Frodo learns of his friends' intention to accompany him.
*[[26 September]]: Frodo and his companions travel through the [[Old Forest]] and come to the House of [[Tom Bombadil]].
*[[28 September]]: The Hobbits are trapped by a [[Barrow-wights|Barrow-wight]]. Frodo resists putting on the Ring.
*[[29 September]]: Frodo meets [[Aragorn]] in [[Bree]].

*[[6 October]]: Frodo is wounded by the [[Witch-king]] at [[Weathertop]].
*[[20 October]]: Frodo crosses the [[Ford of Bruinen]] pursued by the Nazgûl.
*[[23 October]]: [[Elrond]] removes the sliver of the [[Morgul-knife|Morgul-blade]] from Frodo's body.
*[[24 October]]: Frodo wakes in [[Rivendell]].
*[[25 October]]: At the [[Council of Elrond]], Frodo volunteers to take the Ring to [[Mordor]].

*[[25 December]]: Frodo and the [[Fellowship of the Ring|Fellowship]] leave Rivendell.

==[[Third Age 3019|3019]]==
*[[13 January]]: The Fellowship enters [[Moria]].
*[[15 January]]: Gandalf battles the [[Balrogs|Balrog]] and falls into [[shadow]]. The Fellowship enters [[Lothlórien]].
*[[17 January]]: Frodo meets [[Galadriel]].

*[[14 February]]: Frodo looks into the [[Mirror of Galadriel]].
*[[16 February]]: Frodo and the Fellowship leave Lothlórien.
*[[26 February]]: At Amon Hen, [[Boromir]] tries to take the Ring. Frodo decides to go to Mordor alone but is followed by [[Samwise Gamgee|Sam]].
*[[29 February]]: Frodo meets [[Gollum]] and spares his life.

*[[1 March]]-[[2 March]]: Gollum leads the Hobbits through the [[Dead Marshes]].
*[[5 March]]: The Hobbits reach the [[Black Gate]] and realize it's impassable. Frodo agrees to follow Gollum to a [[Cirith Ungol|secret way]] into Mordor.
*[[7 March]]: Frodo meets [[Faramir]], brother of Boromir.
*[[8 March]]: Frodo asks Faramir to spare Gollum's life at the [[Forbidden Pool]]. The Hobbits part company with Faramir in the morning.
*[[9 March]]: The Hobbits reach the [[Morgul-road]] at dusk.
*[[10 March]]: The Hobbits reach the [[Cross-roads]] and continue to the [[Morgul Vale]]. Frodo sees the Witch-king leading an army from [[Minas Morgul]] and resists putting on the Ring.
*[[12 March]]: Gollum leads Frodo and Sam into [[Shelob's Lair]].
*[[13 March]]: Frodo is wounded by [[Shelob]] and is taken prisoner by [[Orcs of Mordor|Orcs]] to the [[Tower of Cirith Ungol]].
*[[14 March]]: Sam finds Frodo in the Tower of Cirith Ungol.
*[[15 March]]: Frodo and Sam escape from the Tower.
*[[16 March]]: Frodo and Sam look toward [[Mount Doom]] from the [[Morgai]].
*[[18 March]]: Frodo and Sam are forced to join a company of Orcs marching toward Udun.
*[[19 March]]: Frodo and Sam escape from the Orcs and continue on.
*[[22 March]]: Frodo and Sam leave the road and turn south toward Mount Doom.
*[[23 March]]: The Hobbits cast away their gear.
*[[24 March]]: The Hobbits reach the foot of Mount Doom.
*[[25 March]]: Frodo reaches the [[Cracks of Doom]] and claims the Ring for himself. Gollum bites off Frodo's finger and falls into the fiery chasm. The Ring is destroyed.

*[[8 April]]: Frodo and Sam are honoured at the [[Field of Cormallen]].

*[[1 May]]: Frodo carries the crown at Aragorn's coronation.

*[[15 July]]: [[Arwen]] tells Frodo that he may pass into the [[Aman|West]] in her stead.

*[[6 October]]: Frodo feels pain in his shoulder on the anniversary of his confrontation with the Witch-king.
*[[30 October]]: The Hobbits arrive at the [[Brandywine Bridge]].

*[[3 November]]: The [[Battle of Bywater]]. Frodo says that [[Saruman]]'s life should be spared, but the Wizard is killed by [[Gríma]].
*[[4 November]]: Frodo agrees to be Deputy Mayor.


==[[Third Age 3020|3020]]==
*[[13 March]]: Frodo is ill on the anniversary of his encounter with Shelob.

*[[1 May]]: Sam marries [[Rosie Cotton]] and moves into Bag End.

*[[Mid-year's Day]]: Frodo resigns as Deputy Mayor.

*[[6 October]]: Frodo is ill again.

==[[Third Age 3021|3021]]==
*[[13 March]]: Frodo is ill again.

*[[21 September]]: Frodo and Sam set out for the [[Grey Havens]].
*[[22 September]]: Frodo meets Galadriel and Elrond in the Woody End.
*[[29 September]]: Frodo sails into the West to the [[Undying Lands]].
